 shape and orient scientific developments old and new. By looking closely at the composition of science epics and the related genres developed along with them, we are able to view the historical narrative of science as a form of knowledge itself, one that discloses much about the development of our understanding of and relationship to science over time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aSciencexHistoriography. 0aSciencexPhilosophy. 0aScience--Historiography. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  acosmic evolution.  adogma of unity.  afinal story.  afinal theory.  agenre of synthesis.  anatural history.  ascientific epic.  ascientific myth.  auniversal history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831107119360 cprintz978022647612440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226500737423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226500737/original  a978-3-11-071193-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles